reviewText: I would classify this movie as being barely "ok'.  I was tempted a couple of times to just cut it off and do something else, but continued watching it in hopes that it would improve.  The acting is basically at an amateur level.

reviewText: After watching half of it I did turn it OFF.I have one word for it as what Leonard Maltin says in his classification'sfor the bottom of the barrel movies-He does not give them even one star, It is not worth even one star from me.Wasted my time and money.

reviewText: This is an action packed Western, with less swearing, and better acting.  Bob Handigan plays a good role in this movie, and after seeing it--I know you won't be disappointed. This movie is a cross between HIGH NOON and TOMBSTONE.

reviewText: claims to be another classic ... well it aint going to happen...actors.. they aint.. sound quality isnt there lacks a lot of luster ..the director must have been asleep during the making of the picture... if u want to call it that ... this is  a film ... that should not have been made ..save ur money .. there is better films out there than this....
Title: The Showdown

reviewText: Considering that this is a very small time production it is not bad, not great but not bad.  Some of the dialog is cheesy as well as the acting.  But all in all not a bad movie.  Also, I know the star Bob Handigan, we go way back, Bob would be so good in a comedy.  I had a hard time taking him serious, cause he rarely is.  It is worth a watch.
Title: The Showdown
